.TH _PRINTF 3 "Custom Library"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom formatted output function

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf() prints output to the standard output according to the format string.
It supports the following conversion specifiers:

.TP
%c
Prints a single character.

.TP
%s
Prints a string.

.TP
%d, %i
Prints a signed decimal integer.

.TP
%%
Prints a literal percent sign.

Unsupported specifiers are printed as "%x" (percent followed by the character).

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed.
Returns -1 if format is NULL or format ends with a single '%'.

.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
_printf("Hello %s, number: %d%%\\n", "World", 42);
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
printf(3)
